    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, cut your <strong>chicken </strong>into strips</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and mix well until evenly coated</p><p>Add your<strong> soy sauce</strong> to the bowl and mix to combine</p><p>Add your<strong> cornflour</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until the chicken is fully coated in the cornflour mixture</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> sriracha</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) with your <strong>mayo</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Remove 2 <strong>outer lettuce leaves </strong>per person and set these aside for serving</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong> in half</p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken strips </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>fried chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Add more oil to the pan if it is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fried-chicken-breast-burger-with-sriracha-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fill the <strong>warmed brioche halves </strong>with the <strong>outer</strong> <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>,<strong> tomato rounds</strong>, <strong>fried chicken </strong>and <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chips </strong>and <strong>lettuce halves </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the lettuce with the <strong>dressing </strong>and serve any <strong>remaining sriracha mayo </strong>to the side for dipping</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
